TOKYO
-LRB- AP -RRB- --
Japanese Foreign Minister Keizo Obuchi on Thursday applauded Britain 's decision to reduce its nuclear warhead arsenal , calling it `` a courageous action . ''
`` We hope the British decision will encourage other countries with nuclear capabilities to accelerate disarmament , '' Obuchi said in a statement .
`` This is a courageous action that we welcome from our hearts , '' he said .
The British government announced Wednesday that it will slash the number of operationally available nuclear warheads on its Trident submarines by one-third to 200 as part of a major defense review .
Japan , the only country in the world to suffer a nuclear attack , recently proposed an international forum on preventing nuclear arms proliferation in the wake of nuclear tests by India and Pakistan .
